 Mariah Carey's All I Want For Christmas has become the first single to hit the number one spot on the Billboard charts over four different decades. The first time she released the single was in 1994 and it was number one. In the 2000s, she re-released it and it topped the charts and reached number one again. In the 2010s she reached the number one spot for the third time and this year, she holds the number one spot from 30 December until 4 January 2020. Her record beat records set by stars such as Michael Jackson, Britney Spears, Elton John, Madonna, Janet Jackson, Christina Aguilera, Steve Wonder and Usher who have all reached the number one spot thrice and three different decades.  Read: MARIAH CAREY FINALLY TOPS BILLBOARD CHARTS! Billboard Charts announced the news on their Twitter page on Monday and excited Mariah retweeted, saying "Yaaaaaaaaay!!! We did it."  .@MariahCarey's "All I Want For Christmas Is You" is officially No. 1 on the #Hot100 for a third week.As this is the first chart of the 2020s, she becomes the first artist in history to rule the chart in four separate decades: 1990s, 2000s, 2010s & 2020s. Yaaaaaaaaay!!! WE. DID. IT. ??????????????But.... what’s a decade? https://t.co/OaNK23GFuN   